Write a python function to calculate the average and standard deviation of a list of numbers
def main():
numbers = [3, 4, 5, 10, 12, 8]
average = sum(numbers)/len(numbers)
print("Average:", average)
std_dev = math.sqrt((sum([(x-average)*(x-average) for x in numbers]) / (len(numbers)-1)) * ((1/len(numbers)) - 0))
print("Standard Deviation:", std_dev)
